    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"816344\">Aaron Liu</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/113489-new-members/topic/calc.20xy/near/525539554\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>So first I was thinking that I need to get rid of the <code>y</code>, and the only way to do that is to rewrite using <code>h2</code>. But to rewrite with <code>h2</code> I need <code>y</code> to be multiplied by <code>x</code>. So I see from <code>h1</code> that <code>x = 2</code> need <code>-1/2</code> copies of <code>h2</code> to rewrite with. Then I used <code>h1</code> to spawn in the <code>x</code> and then <code>h2</code> to eliminate the <code>y</code>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I think I just need to understand this to get how Aaron did it. Processing...</p>",
