        "sender_full_name": "Răzvan Flavius Panda",
        "timestamp": 1750780429
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"374664\">Răzvan Flavius Panda</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/113489-new-members/topic/calc.20xy/near/525549464\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"816344\">Aaron Liu</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/113489-new-members/topic/calc.20xy/near/525549217\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Once someone else asked how the sum of squares could be negative</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Complex numbers I'm guessing.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>They're rational</p>",
        "id": 525549494,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1750780441
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>What? That doesn't sound rational.</p>",
        "id": 525549567,
        "sender_full_name": "Răzvan Flavius Panda",
        "timestamp": 1750780467
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And yet you just proved it</p>",
        "id": 525549627,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1750780487
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>well false implies false so you're fine</p>",
        "id": 525549680,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1750780504
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes, I see. What the hell is happening.</p>",
        "id": 525549683,
        "sender_full_name": "Răzvan Flavius Panda",
        "timestamp": 1750780505
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So how does a sum of rational squares end up negative? What magic is that?</p>",
        "id": 525549792,
        "sender_full_name": "Răzvan Flavius Panda",
        "timestamp": 1750780546
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>it just means there's no actual values of p q r that can satisfy the assumptions, but the algebraic manipulations you did are still valid</p>",
        "id": 525549873,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1750780579
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>in terms of CS, this is called garbage in garbage out (GIGO)</p>",
        "id": 525549920,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1750780598
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I am lost, I don't understand.</p>",
        "id": 525550114,
        "sender_full_name": "Răzvan Flavius Panda",
        "timestamp": 1750780656
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://www.desmos.com/3d/oopchza16y\">https://www.desmos.com/3d/oopchza16y</a></p>",
        "id": 525550157,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1750780671
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>look at the 3d plot, the two surfaces have no intersection</p>",
        "id": 525550185,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1750780681
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"374664\">Răzvan Flavius Panda</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/113489-new-members/topic/calc.20xy/near/525550114\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I am lost, I don't understand.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>if I give you the hypothesis that 2x^2 = -2, then you can do algebraic manipulations to deduce x^2 = -1. There is no actual rational number that can make this happen, but the algebraic manipulations you did are still valid</p>",
        "id": 525550320,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1750780729
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>2x^2 = -2 will always imply x^2 = -1, even if there is no x that can satisfy it</p>",
        "id": 525550417,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1750780764
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>so there are no x, y, z that satisfy both hypotheses?</p>",
        "id": 525550616,
        "sender_full_name": "Răzvan Flavius Panda",
        "timestamp": 1750780824
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>as another example, x^2+x+1 = 0 implies x^3 = 1, but there are no rational numbers that satisfy x^2+x+1=0.</p>",
        "id": 525550648,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1750780835
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"374664\">Răzvan Flavius Panda</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/113489-new-members/topic/calc.20xy/near/525550616\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>so there are no x, y, z that satisfy both hypotheses?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>That's the point of the 3d graph, where you can see that there are no real solutions</p>",
        "id": 525550734,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1750780859
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I am being a bit mindblown now. So... I did a proof, on 2 hypotheses that can not both be true and ended up with garbage or something.</p>",
        "id": 525550887,
        "sender_full_name": "Răzvan Flavius Panda",
        "timestamp": 1750780902
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Here's an example proof that no <code>p, q, r</code> can satisfy the hypotheses</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">¬∃</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">p</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">q</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">r</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℚ</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">p</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">q</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">r</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∧</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">p</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">q</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">p</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">r</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">q</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">r</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">intro</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⟨</span><span class=\"n\">p</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">q</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">r</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h1</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h2</span><span class=\"bp\">⟩</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">suffices</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">p</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">q</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">r</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"mi\">4</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">nlinarith</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">calc</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">p</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">q</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">r</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span>\n<span class=\"w\">      </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">p</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">q</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">r</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">p</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">q</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">p</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">r</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">q</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">r</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ring</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">h1</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h2</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"mi\">4</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ring</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 525551187,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1750780984
    },
